AGI - The Israeli army withdrew all ground troops from the south of the Gaza Strip, after four consecutive months of fighting in the area of Khan Younis. The presence of the military in the Strip was greatly reduced. For the moment, the Nahal Brigade remains operating in the area, which secures the 'Netzarim corridor', the road that divides the Gaza Strip.
&nbsp;
Tens of thousands of Israelis protested on Saturday evening against Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu> while the Israeli war against Hamas in Gaza reached six months. The organizers of the event said that "about 100 thousand" people > gathered in a Tel Aviv intersection called "Piazza della Democrazia" after mass protests against controversial judicial reforms last year.&nbsp; Some people were injured, one of which severely.
&nbsp;
By shouting "elections now", > the protesters asked for the resignation Netanyahu. Protected also in other cities, with Israeli opposition leader Yair Lapid> who took part in a demonstration in Kfar Saba before his departure for talks in Washington>. "They didn't learn anything, they didn't change," he said adding that "until we send them home, they won't give this country the chance to move on."
&nbsp;
The Israeli media reported that clashes broke out between protesters and police > in the Tel Aviv rally ended with an arrest. The families of Hamas prisoners in Gaza joined the protest.&nbsp;
