AGI - The dam collapsed in Orsk>, in the Russian Ural area, has yielded due to delays in maintenance. The regional prosecutor's office is investigating the collapse, which caused three deaths at the moment, in addition to the evacuation of 1,164 people (including 336 children) and the flooding of over 2,500 houses. The evacuates were addressed "to temporary reception centers. "The dam collapsed on 5 April 2024, > because the measures aimed at maintaining in good technical state its hydrotechnical equipment were not taken in time," said the prosecutor.
The structure was set up in 2010. "The branches of the State Technical Supervisory Authority have previously identified breaches in the maintenance of the dam and have been sent notes to the competent authority on this," said the prosecutor's office.
<div </div
&nbsp;
In particular, in the last month the prosecutor sent to the first deputy mayor of Orsk "a warning about the inadmissibility of the violation of the law on the protection of the population and the territories from the situations of natural emergency and caused by man". Two days ago the state of emergency was declared in the Orenburg region because of the deterioration of the flood situation, 495 temporary accommodation facilities were deployed in total with a capacity of more than 82,300 people.&nbsp; the regional authorities, for their part, also cited the dissolution of the snows that cause "the rise" of the rivers of the region - including the Urals. "The level of water (of the Ural River) will continue to rise," warned the mayor of the city of Orenburg, Sergei Salmine. "The level could reach a critical threshold," he added, inviting "all to leave immediately the houses located in the flooded area" before having to use the "force". The floods due to the dissolution of snow also affect Kazakhstan, a country bordering Russia. In a speech to the nation, President Kassym-Jomart Tokayev spoke of "a natural disaster", "perhaps the largest, in terms of size and consequences, of the last 80 years".&nbsp;
&nbsp;

